OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNational Living Wage set to
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frise to #9.50 an hour      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Workers on the minimum wage are set to 
OL,6, get a pay boost from April, with the   
OL,7, rate for those aged over 23 rising to  
OL,8, #9.50 an hour from #8.91.              
OL,10,FThe rise means a full-time worker will 
OL,11,Fget #1,074 extra a year before tax.    
OL,13,FThe move will be announced at this     
OL,14,Fweek's Budget and follows the          
OL,15,Frecommendation of independent advisers,
OL,16,Fthe Low Pay Commission.                
OL,18,FThe government has faced pressure to   
OL,19,Fhelp low-paid, younger workers, who are
OL,20,Famong the worst hit by the pandemic.   
